article.headline: Charting a strong September start, Nasdaq (briefly) ventures atop 12,000 mark
article.body: U.S. stocks are mixed early Wednesday, vacillating in the wake of an initially strong September start. Against this backdrop, the S&P 500 has extended a persistent break to record territory, while the Nasdaq Composite has briefly ventured atop the 12,000 mark for the first time on record. Before detailing the U.S. markets’ wider view,...
